{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1778260850,"nonce":"3+G5/3Ew0R/FewY1vWgodkQcY2g=","title":"Full-state ε adversary class matching C\u0026S Eq. 13 H∞ disturbance","message":"Stage 4 in the proposed regulator-coupling / decoupling-chain programme (exploration, not committed). Prerequisite for stages 4–6; depends on eval-pipeline audit (4469cae) and linear-baseline issue (d448c9d).\n\n**Question.** Is the trained controller's Δv direction caused by the adversary-class mismatch between LinearDynamicsAdversary (constant per-trial ΔA, Frobenius-bounded, time-invariant within trial) and the C\u0026S H∞ formulation (free time-varying ε_t ∈ ℝ⁶, L2-bounded over rollout)?\n\n**Approach.** Add a new adversary class to the training pipeline that matches C\u0026S Eq. 13: a free time-varying ε_t ∈ ℝⁿ per step, with L2 norm bounded across the rollout (∑_t ||ε_t||² ≤ budget). Implementation: parametric per-step ε_t(θ_adv) trained via PGD in the augmented state, analogous to LinearDynamicsAdversary but per-step. Train linear-regulator, linear-tracker, and GRU under this adversary.\n\n**Round-trip identity test.** A linear regulator trained under this adversary should converge to the Riccati controller up to optimisation noise; its Δv should match the analytical +1.0% (C\u0026S regime) or +10.8% (rlrmp regime). Compute γ_net via the induced-gain analyser and compare to γ_*. Round-trip failure means training is broken; round-trip success means any RNN deviation is genuinely architectural.\n\n**Falsification.** If GRU under matched adversary still gives Δv ≈ 0, decoupling-via-architecture is robust to adversary class. If Δv shifts toward Riccati prediction, the previous −25% was largely a LinearDynamicsAdversary-mismatch artefact.\n\n**Cross-refs.** Plan §3 stage 4. C\u0026S Eq. 13. LinearDynamicsAdversary in training codebase. Training-methods coord c99ad9d. Adversary strategy verification 89891ab (prerequisite).","files":null}]}